Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the inauguration of a task force on online harassment and abuse. She acknowledged the survivors of online abuse and commended their bravery. Harris emphasized the importance of standing together and supporting those who have experienced online harassment. She shared her experiences as a prosecutor dealing with crimes affecting women and children and expressed the need to update laws to address the harm caused by cyber exploitation. Harris highlighted the mental health consequences of cyberstalking and the role of online hate and abuse in acts of mass violence. She also discussed the potential risks to privacy and personal data in the context of overturning Roe v. Wade. The task force aims to modernize the government's response to online harassment and abuse, develop evidence-informed policies, and secure federal funding for addressing the issue. Harris called for a collective effort from the government, law enforcement, and the tech sector to address the problem urgently.